Types of Encoding :

Categorical varibales:
          Eg : sex= "male" , "female" thisis categorical varibales
          
1)           Nominal Encoding (eg gender or state )
2)           Ordinal Encoding (eg rearrange categorical data based on rank like eduction qulification )


Nominal Encoding :
                  One hot encoding
                  One hot encoding with many categorical variable
                  Mean Encoding and also more
                  
Ordinal Encoding :
                  label encoding
                  target guided ordinal encoding
                  
                  
                  
ONE HOT ENCODING 


  Eg state : germany,france,spain  based on categorical data that many colums will be create
  this case 3 columns are create 1 in intersection of data or diagonals are 1 others are    1 
  

Label Encoding  (odinal encoding)
  
  
   Education BE,       1
             Master,   2
             Phd,      3 
             Statician 4
             
             
One hot encoding with multiple categorical varibale

   KDD orange reference
   
   if categorical data contains duplicated we ignore duplicates and create unique    columns             
   
   
Target Guided ordinal encoding


     calculate mean value for every categorical varibale 
     based on mean value rearrange features
     

Mean Encoding 


     if we feature A B C D E  w.r.t o/p 1 0 1 0 1
     calculate mean with respect to ouput 
     just replace the categorical varible to respective rank
     
     real time application is pincode data set
     if we have 10000 pincode we cant create 10000 columns 
     based on means of feature value we can use that data     
 
             
             
  
                    
